pesticide.PPE: Applicators and other handlers must wear: Long-sleeved shirt and long pants; Shoes plus socks. After the product has been loaded into properly calibrated application equipment, shirt, pants, socks, and shoes are sufficient Personal Protective Equipment.
pesticide.trade_Name: DuPont Acelepryn 0.067% Insecticide Plus LESCO Fertilizer

Safety_Information.general_Info: Causes moderate eye irritation. Avoid contact with eyes or clothing. Wash thoroughly with soap and water after handling and before eating, drinking, chewing gum or using tobacco.
Safety_Information.if_In_Eyes: Hold eye open and rinse slowly and gently with water for 15-20 minutes. Remove contact lenses, if present, after the first 5 minutes, then continue rinsing eye. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
Safety_Information.physician_Note: Have the container or label with you when calling a poison control center or doctor or going for treatment. You may also contact CHEMTREC 1-800-424-9300 for emergency medical treatment information.
